*       HOB - Risky Business:

o   A study of real estate performance amidst past economic downturns is in=
structive, but every recession is different. A look at REIT betas during ri=
sk-off days this year when equities and bond yields both declined offers in=
sight on where risk lies today. A hallmark of the recession potentially on =
the horizon is a reversal of Covid winners and losers. The high-flying sect=
ors of the past two and a half years appear to possess outsized risk today =
and vice versa.

*       Apartment Sector - Valuation Changes:

o   Apartment fundamentals are healthy today, but the combination of 1) hig=
her financing costs and 2) greater uncertainty around the future trajectory=
 of rents amidst weakening economic growth, is causing incremental softness=
 in the apartment transaction market. Green Street's apartment cap rates ar=
e increased ~15 bps across markets, resulting in a 3.5% decline in values.

The referenced reports can be accessed via this link:  https://greenst.box.=
